what are different headings in html

<h1>-------<h6>


 ----------  ------- -----------------------------------
 what is CSS
 css-cascading style sheets
       -USED TO STYLE/DESIGN webpages
       -to apply css to element we need to use style attributes
       syntax :
       < style ="property: value;property2:value2"> content</style>


1.inline css
     syntax:
     <style="property:value ; property2:value2"></style>
     -used to style specific elements only


2.internal css-cascading
   syntax:
   <style>
    selector{
        property:value;
        property2:value2
    }
    -used to style multiple elements
   </style> 
   
   3.external css-cascading
     1.create a css file eith .css extension
     2.link the css file to the html file
     3.used to style multiple pages(large scale projects)

   syntax:
      <html>
      <head>

        <link rel="stylesheet" href="filename.css">
   

   inline css>internal css>external css

based on display we have two types of elements

1.block level elements
2.inline elements

1.block level---the element will occupy entire width of the page
                 eg:p,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6

2.inline----the element will occupy its respective space in the page
             eg:i,small


to change dispaly property of an attribute we use display attribute
<p style="display:inline"></p>   ---inline level  

----------------------------------------------------
margin:
-the space around the border
-margin attribute
syntax:
h1{
    margin:20px(all sides top bottom left right)
    margin:20px(top/bottom) 15px(left/right)
    margin:20px(top)  30px(right) 40px(bottom)  50px(left)
    margin-top:
    margin-bottom:
    margin left:
    margin right:

}
 shorthand :
      margin : top right bottom left
      ----------------------------------------

padding:
-space around the content
-padding attribute   
h1{
   padding:20px(all sides top bottom left right)
   padding:20px(top/bottom) 15px(left/right)
    padding:20px(top)  30px(right) 40px(bottom)  50px(left)
    padding-top:
    padding-bottom:
    padding left:
    padding right:

}
 shorthand :
      padding : top right bottom left
      ----------------------------------------
border:
--border attribute

syntax:
h1{
   
   border-style:
   border-color:
   border size
   border:size style color(all sides)
   border top
   border bottom
   border left
   border right
   border radius for rounded corners

}
style:
1.solid
2.dotted
3.double
4.dashed
5.ridge
6.groove
insert
outset

----------------------------------------------------
box model in css-cascading
-it describes how elements are structured and spaced in web page


structure;
    content(text/image/video/audio)--->padding(space around the content)-->border(outline around the content)--->margin(space outside the border,it helps to seperate elements)


